<poem>
<coder>TL</coder>
<header>
    <title>Southern Mansion</title>
    <byLine poet="Bontemps_A">Arna Bontemps</byLine>
</header>
<content>

<line n="1" stanza="1">Poplars are standing there still as death </line>
<line n="2" stanza="1">And ghosts of dead men </line>
<line n="3" stanza="1">Meet their ladies walking </line>
<line n="4" stanza="1">Two by two beneath the shade </line>
<line n="5" stanza="1">And standing on the marble steps<punc type="period">.</punc></line>

<line n="6" stanza="2">There is a sound of music echoing </line>
<line n="7" stanza="2">Through the open door </line>
<line n="8" stanza="2">And in the field there is </line>
<line n="9" stanza="2">Another sound tinkling in the cotton<punc type="colon">:</punc> </line>
<line n="10" stanza="2">Chains of bondmen dragging on the ground<punc type="period">.</punc></line>

<line n="11" stanza="3">The years go back with an iron clank<punc type="comma">,</punc> </line>
<line n="12" stanza="3">A hand is on the gate<punc type="comma">,</punc> </line>
<line n="13" stanza="3">A dry leaf trembles on the wall<punc type="period">.</punc> </line>
<line n="14" stanza="3">Ghosts are walking<punc type="period">.</punc> </line>
<line n="15" stanza="3">They have broken roses down </line>
<line n="16" stanza="3">And poplars stand there still as death<punc type="period">.</punc></line>
</content>
</poem>
